  "title": "Specifying min or max value for RangeInput refines automatically on this value",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nWhen using RangeInput, if setting a value for min or max, this value is automatically refined :\n```tsx\n<Panel header=\"price\">\n    <RangeInput attribute=\"price\" max={99999} />\n</Panel>\n```\n\n<img width=\"501\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/89788eaa-7f9a-4944-b70c-d08db57345b1\" />\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open the sandbox\n2. See that current refinement includes price even if user did not refine any value\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/romantic-wilson-4ypmhs?file=%2Fsrc%2FApp.tsx%3A58%2C23\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nIt should only change the allowed bounds, not refine on max value\n\n### Package version\n\nalgolia@4, react-instantsearch@7.15.4\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
